  "screenContent": {
    "screen 1": {
      "title": "PROBLEM STATEMENT",
      "body": [
        "The Challenge in 3D Scene Creation",
        "",
        "- Complexity Barrier: Existing 3D tools have steep learning curves that discourage students and beginners from learning interactive 3D composition",
        "- Accessibility Gap: Most professional 3D software requires installation, licensing, and powerful hardware limiting access for educational environments",
        "- Collaboration Friction: Sharing 3D projects between team members typically involves file transfers, version conflicts, and permission headaches",
        "- Export Limitations: Converting 3D scenes into standalone, portable web experiences often requires complex pipeline knowledge",
        "- No Lightweight Browser Solution: There is a lack of integrated, browser-based 3D editors that combine creation, management, and export in one platform",
        "",
        "\"Students, instructors, and designers need a lightweight, browser-based 3D editor that lowers the barrier to entry while supporting the full workflow from creation to export.\""
      ]
    }
  },
